phpgacl
-------

* Unpack phpgacl-vx.x.x into the libs/ directory.

* Move libs/phpgacl/adodb/ to libs/

* Edit libs/phpgacl/gacl.class.php and set ADODB_DIR correctly to
  the new path.

* In the same file, insert the following code near the top of the file: 

unset($options);
include(dirname(__FILE__).'/../../admin/config.inc.php');
$options['db_type']     = $cfg['db_type'];
$options['db_host']     = $cfg['db_host'];
$options['db_user']     = $cfg['db_usr'];
$options['db_name']     = $cfg['db_name'];
$options['db_password'] = $cfg['db_pass'];
$gacl_options['smarty_dir'] = dirname(__FILE__).'/../smarty';
$gacl_options['smarty_template_dir'] = 'templates';
$gacl_options['smarty_compile_dir'] = dirname(__FILE__).'/../smarty/templates_c';

* In the same file, declare $options global by inserting this line:

global $options;

  into the function gacl().

* Move libs/phpgacl/admin/smarty/ to libs/

* mkdir libs/smarty/templates_c && chmod 777 libs/smarty/templates_c/

* Hopfully libs/phpgacl/setup.php was not changed, otherwise you have to
  implement the same changes in admin/setup.php.

* Edit admin/setup.php so that PHPGACL_DIR points to the new version of phpgacl.

* Edit admin/index.php so that PHPGACL_DIR points to the new version of phpgacl.

* Drop all database tables.

* Reinitialize spiff using admin/setup.php.

* Make sure that libs/phpgacl/admin/acl_admin.php works in your browser.
